                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="67202" author="pjones" created="Sun, 22 Sep 2013 13:17:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;removed FixVersion for this tracking ticket. Each subtask is given its own FixVersion to reflect its priority&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64373" author="jay" created="Thu, 15 Aug 2013 22:45:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7346&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7346&lt;/a&gt; is to fix a defect can cause compatibility problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="63680" author="jay" created="Mon, 5 Aug 2013 22:23:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com7243&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com7243&lt;/a&gt; will fix the sub-tasks 1, 3 and 8.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="63186" author="jay" created="Mon, 29 Jul 2013 20:31:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/6794&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/6794&lt;/a&gt; is pushed to support dropping caching pages by ll_data_version().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="63099" author="jay" created="Sun, 28 Jul 2013 23:32:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7159&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7159&lt;/a&gt; is pushed to fix a problem of ioc_copy_end.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="63056" author="jay" created="Fri, 26 Jul 2013 16:33:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In mdc_close(), if mdc_fid_alloc() fails, we should remember this error code, therefore if close REQ finishes successfully, that error code should be returned upper layer to LLITE to indicate why release failed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="63055" author="jay" created="Fri, 26 Jul 2013 16:31:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We need to land patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/6794&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/6794&lt;/a&gt; for HSM so that ll_data_version() can drop all caching pages before doing release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
